        IN_REALITY_THOUGH_SNIFFLE_YOU_VE_HAD_ME                                 = 10853,  -- In reality, though, <sniffle> you've had me in your heartarus all along... Waaah!
        SORRY_TOTO_WE_WOULD_VE_SAID_SOMETHING_TO                                = 10854,  -- Sorry, Toto. We would've said something to help brace you, but didn't want to spoil the element of surprrrise!
        I_HAVE_TO_SAY_THAT_I_EXPECTED_OUR                                       = 10855,  -- I have to say that I expected our gift to bring a smile to your face, not tears to your eyes.
        IT_S_JUST_THAT_I_BELIEVED_YOU_WERE                                      = 10856,  -- It's just that...I believed you were avoiding me...so...
        I_DESPERATELY_WANTED_TO_TELL_YOU_IN_ADVANCE                             = 10857,  -- I desperately wanted to tell you in advance, but Fhelm was dead set against it!
        I_HAD_NO_CHOICE_YOU_D_RRRAISE_THE                                       = 10858,  -- I had no choice! You'd rrraise the fur on your back and hiss at us if we mentioned anything about a present.
        I_I_M_TOUCH_WOUCHED_TO_THINK_THAT                                       = 10859,  -- I...I'm touch-wouched. To think that I ever wanted to throw away my life as an adventurer...
        I_VE_SAID_SO_MANY_TERRIBLE_WERRIBLE_THINGS                              = 10860,  -- I've said so many terrible-werrible things, but...if you'd find it within yourselves to take me back...
        OF_COURSE_WE_DO_OUR_BONDS_OF_FRIENDSHIP                                 = 10861,  -- Of course we do! Our bonds of friendship run deeper than the Sea of Shu'Meyo!
        THE_NEXT_TIME_YOU_RE_AT_A_LOSS                                          = 10862,  -- The next time you're at a loss for an answer, remember to look to our collective love nestled deep inside you. It'll warm your soul like no other!
        I_CAN_T_THANK_YOU_SNIFFLE_ENOUGH                                        = 10863,  -- I can't thank you...<sniffle>...enough...
        YOU_WILL_ALWAYS_HAVE_A_SPOT_BEHIND_MY                                   = 10864,  -- You will always have a spot behind my back, Nantoto, ever since you saved me from certain death.
        I_STILL_HAVE_THE_IMAGE_OF_THAT_DAY                                      = 10865,  -- I still have the image of that day freshly imprintarued on my mind. We were fighting some harebrained warriors in the Valkurm Dunes--
        COULD_YOU_PLEASE_USE_A_MORE_FLATTERING_WORD                             = 10866,  -- Could you please use a more flattering word like audacious or venturous? Otherwise, it makes me sound doubly pathetic for almost dying at their hands.
        YOU_MANAGED_TO_PRY_ME_FROM_DEATH_S                                      = 10867,  -- You managed to pry me from death's icy grip, but we still had to flee in order to fight another day.
        AND_I_MET_YOU_ON_THE_HUNT_RRRIGHT                                       = 10868,  -- And I met you on the hunt, rrright? Oh, how we used to fight like cats from dusk to dawn.
        HAHAHA_WE_SURE_DID_I_REMEMBER_HAVING_THE                                = 10869,  -- Hahaha, we sure did. I remember having the most heated of argumentarus with you, then crying to Isakoth and Ervok afterwards.
        ASSIDUITY_AND_OPPORTUNITY_ARE_ONE_S_MOST_POWERFUL                       = 10870,  -- Assiduity and opportunity are one's most powerful assets on the path to enlightenment. The knowledge you gain from your travels across continents will be key to unlocking the gates to uncharted territories.
        EXPLORATION_IS_THE_TESTIMONY_TO_ONE_S_COURAGE                           = 10871,  -- Exploration is the testimony to one's courage. Likewise, Records of Eminence objectives are testimony to mankind's inquisitiveness.
        MYRIAD_THOUGHTS_FEELINGS_AND_RECOLLECTIONS_ARE_SCATTERED_OVER           = 10872,  -- Myriad thoughts, feelings, and recollections are scattered over this vast land. We thus calmly gather them into our arms and release them anew unto the adventuring masses. We pay the price for our meddling, but so too do we reap the rewards. We dare, therefore we are.
        I_COULD_NOT_HAVE_SAID_IT_BETTER_MYSELF                                  = 10873,  -- I could not have said it better myself!
        THE_INFLUENCE_EACH_OF_YOU_EXERTS_DURING_YOUR                            = 10874,  -- The influence each of you exerts during your eminent activities may be small in and of itself.
        HOWEVER_THOSE_TO_WHOM_YOU_PROVIDE_SUCCOR_DEEPLY                         = 10875,  -- However, those to whom you provide succor deeply appreciate your tireless efforts.
        MOREOVER_YOU_DO_NOT_PROVIDE_AID_EXCLUSIVELY_TO                          = 10876,  -- Moreover, you do not provide aid exclusively to single individuals. Entire organizations also place their trust in you.
        MANY_WITHIN_THE_A_M_A_N_POSSESS                                         = 10877,  -- Many within the A.M.A.N. possess financial resources the average commoner could only dream of. A chance opportunity from one of these individuals could yield untold riches.
        IT_IS_THEREFORE_NO_STRETCH_OF_THE_IMAGINATION                           = 10878,  -- It is therefore no stretch of the imagination to say that we are able to subsist due to the noble work ethic of adventurers like you.
        IN_OTHER_WORDS_SCRATCH_A_M_A_N                                          = 10879,  -- In other words...scratch A.M.A.N.'s back, and it will scratch yours.
        I_COULD_NOT_HAVE_SAID_IT_BETTER_MYSELF_2                                = 10880,  -- I could not have said it better myself!
        FOR_EXAMPLE_YOU_HAVE_ALSO_MADE_A_PILGRIMAGE                             = 10881,  -- For example, you have also made a pilgrimage to various telepoints scattered about the four corners of Vana'diel and dispersed the darkness that enshrouded the Eldieme Necropolis.
        THESE_TWO_OBJECTIVES_WERE_BOTH_ORIGINALLY_ISSUED_BY                     = 10882,  -- These two objectives were both originally issued by a certain member of the San d'Orian elite.
        IN_CONTRAST_THE_ONE_NANTOTO_REQUESTED_REGARDING_AN                      = 10883,  -- In contrast, the one Nantoto requested regarding an ouka ranman cannot be described as anything but an abnormality.
        THAT_WAS_ONE_WHICH_I_HAD_TO_WORK                                        = 10884,  -- That was one which I had to work behind the scenes to enact. If my memory serves me, you chose % as the spot in which to unleash your explosion of memories, correct?
        HEH_FEAR_NOT_FOR_ONLY_YOU_AND_I                                         = 10885,  -- Heh, fear not, for only you and I know that you consider that place a sanctuary. I will not tell a soul.
        NOR_WILL_I_TELL_ANYONE_ABOUT_THE_VALOR                                  = 10886,  -- Nor will I tell anyone about the valor you displayed in defeating the Yagudo High Priests to complete Grudge.
        HOWEVER_I_SUPPOSE_NANTOTO_ALREADY_KNOWS_THAT                            = 10887,  -- ...However, I suppose Nantoto already knows that.
        ID_10888                                                                = 10888,  -- %!
        I_CAN_T_ADEQUATARULY_EXPRESS_HOW_MUCH_I                                 = 10889,  -- I can't adequataruly express how much I owe you for taking out those Yagudo!
        LISTEN_WE_VE_ALL_DECIDED_WIDED_TO_GO                                    = 10890,  -- Listen, we've all decided-wided to go to %...
        WE_WANT_TO_CHECK_ON_SOME_REPORTARUS_CONCERNING                          = 10891,  -- We want to check on some reportarus concerning a humongous dragon that supposedly patrols the skies there.
        WE_VE_HEARD_VARIOUS_RUMORS_ABOUT_A_SPECIFIC                             = 10892,  -- We've heard various rumors about a specific locale there where bounding insectarus gather. Hopefully we'll be able to find it.
        THERE_S_A_MOUNTAIN_OF_HEARSAY_ABOUT_A                                   = 10893,  -- There's a mountain of hearsay about a flower there that floatarus in midair. I certainly want to see if it's actually real or not.
        THERE_YOU_ARE_I_VE_BEEN_LOOKING_WOOKING                                 = 10894,  -- There you are! I've been looking-wooking all over for you.
        I_RECEIVED_A_COUPLE_LETTARUS_ADDRESSED_TO_YOU                           = 10895,  -- I received a couple lettarus addressed to you.
        THEY_ALL_COME_IN_UNIQUELY_COLORED_ENVELOPE_WENVELOPES                   = 10896,  -- They all come in...uniquely colored envelope-wenvelopes and are signed D. What do you want to do with them?
        OPEN_WHICH_ONE_NONE_FOR_THE_NONCE_THE                                   = 10897,  -- Open which one? None for the nonce. The white one. The green one. The silver one. The purple one. The black one. The blue one. The gold one. The yellow one. The brown one. The red one. The rainbow one.
        I_WOULDN_T_OPEN_ANY_IF_I_WERE                                           = 10898,  -- I wouldn't open any if I were you, either. You never know what crazy-wazy stuff people deliver these days. I'd feel bad about throwing another person's property away, though, so I'll hold onto them for safekeeping.
        HERE_YOU_GO_I_HOPE_IT_DOESN_T                                           = 10899,  -- Here you go. I hope it doesn't contain anything too suspectaru.
        THE_ENVELOPE_CONTAINS_A_BRIEFING_FOR_A_NEW                              = 10900,  -- The envelope contains a briefing for a new objective.
        DON_TCHA_THINK_DAT_FURROWED_BROW_AND_COCKED                             = 10901,  -- Don'tcha think dat furrowed brow and cocked head o' yers escaped me. Yer int'rested in dis chest, ain'tcha? Well, ya gots good right tah be, 'cause even us Gobbies is fascimanated wit' it. It's some sorta myst'ry box salvaged from a shipwreck in da Gugru Blue! Da mysterious part is dat what goes in don't necessarilies come out!
        WHILE_I_MAY_TOUT_ITS_AMAZIN_NESS_DON                                    = 10902,  -- While I may tout its amazin'ness, don'tcha think fer even a second dat I's at liberty tah divulge hows we came by it. Still, I likes yer face. It's a kind face, one dat says ya won't stabs me in da back, which is more'n I can say fer my own mum. Lemme shows ya how to use dis myst'ry box.
        BAH_DAH_BAH_DAHM_DAH_DAAAHM_YA_OPEN                                     = 10903,  -- Bah-dah-bah-dahm dah-daaahm! Ya open da chest. Dat's it. And da kicker be dat I'm da one doin' da openin'. Ya just gets tah stand dere gawkin' in astonishmament. Easy gig, no?
        OH_YEAH_FORE_I_FORGET_WHAT_GOOD_S                                       = 10904,  -- Oh yeah, 'fore I forget. What good's a chest if ya ain't gots da key? Well, da key to dis chest is da fine art o' waitin'.
        YA_WANTSA_KNOW_DA_HOWS_N_DA_WHYS                                        = 10905,  -- Ya wantsa know da hows n' da whys? Well da bosses had our tinkers tinkerin' on troo' da night and dey foun' dat...
        WELL_DEY_FOUN_DAT_WE_REALLY_GOTS_NO                                     = 10906,  -- Well, dey foun' dat we really gots no idea why da loot changes. Anywho, ya's wanna wait 'n wait 'n wait, den keep on waitin' some more. "Good things come tah dose who wait," right? Well, da longer ya wait, da gooder da thing...maybe. Ya just never know wit' a myst'ry box.
        ALSO_I_CALLS_DA_AMOUNT_O_TIME_YA                                        = 10907,  -- Also, I calls da amount o' time ya's waited yer circa...circama...circamadamian...ugh, yer daily tally. It ain't just da name dat's catchy, though. Da higher yer tally, da gooder yer goods get! Can't get much good--er, simpler dan dat.
        FINALLY_YA_OPENS_DA_CHEST_OOOH_I_CAN                                    = 10908,  -- Finally, ya opens da chest. Oooh, I can barely contain m'self thinkin' o' all da riches I--er, ya could have!
        OH_DAT_S_RIGHT_HEYHEYHEY_GOT_ANY_ITEMS                                  = 10909,  -- Oh, dat's right! Heyheyhey, got any items ya won't be needin'? If so, fork 'em over 'n yer daily tally'll increase! Mebbe not by much, but dat's better'n nothin', am I right?
        AND_DERE_S_NO_BETTER_FEELIN_DAN_TAKIN                                   = 10910,  -- And dere's no better feelin' dan takin' trash and turnin' it into treasure. It's pramactically a new kind o' alchemy! But don't go gung ho 'n overfills da thing 'til its hinges break. Myst'ry boxes don't grow on goobbues, y'know.
        PLUS_I_LL_BE_HERE_TAH_STOPS_YA                                          = 10911,  -- Plus, I'll be here tah stops ya if I sees ya stuffin' whole Gobbiebags worth o' possessions in dere, so don't worry yer oversized noggin' over and over over it. Whats was I sayin' again? Ugh, never mind.
        SADLY_HOWSEVER_ANODDA_MYST_RY_BOUT_DIS_CHEST                            = 10912,  -- Sadly, howsever, anodda myst'ry 'bout dis chest is dat it won't takes just any ol' bauble. It has da taste o' a picky peiste--it feasts upon nothin' but da rarest and unique-est o' artifacts.
        LASTLY_SINCE_WE_DON_T_KNOWS_WHERE_DA                                    = 10913,  -- Lastly, since we don't knows where da items go once inside, ya ain't gettin' nothin' back datcha put in. Ya reap whatcha sow, and da weather ain't always condusimasive to a good harvest, am I right? My condolemances in advance for any losses ya mights incur from da myst'ry box's fickle nature.
        DAT_ALL_MAKE_NOUGH_SENSE_TAH_YA_JUST                                    = 10914,  -- Dat all make 'nough sense tah ya? Just say da woid when ya wanna use my services. I's more'n happy tah help.
        HEY_I_REM_MBER_SEEIN_YER_FOICE_ROUND                                    = 10915,  -- Hey! I rem'mber seein' yer foice 'round here. Take a looksie. I's taken' it upon myself tah jigger 'round wit' dese all-new myst'ry boxes, found straight from an ol' capsized vessel in the Gugru Blue.
        I_S_NEVAH_GONNA_SAY_HOW_WE_GOTS                                         = 10916,  -- I's nevah gonna say how we gots our hands on 'em, so dun even ask! But, still, I gots tah say dat dese're somet'in' special! Now try yer hand 'fore I smack ya!
        JUST_SELECT_YER_DESIR_D_DIAL_AND_PLUG                                   = 10917,  -- Just select yer desir'd dial and plug 'way at it. Will ya win somethin' super special? Or will't be da booby proize?
        DESE_RE_SOME_SPECIAL_DIALS_AN_I_GOTS                                    = 10918,  -- Dese're some special dials, an' I gots no inklin' what's inside. Ya gots tah open 'em yerself tah find out what treasures lie within!
        OH_HO_I_S_FORGETTIN_TAH_EXPLAIN_SOMETHIN                                = 10919,  -- Oh ho, I's forgettin' tah explain somethin' to ya. See dese special dials? Dey're super primo, but I still no know wut's gonna be in dere.
        SO_I_S_NOT_BE_TAKIN_NO_RESPONSIBILITY                                   = 10920,  -- So I's not be takin' no responsibility if somethin' weird 'n wacky comes out. Got it? Ya open it, ya keep it.
        N_OPENIN_EM_REQUIRES_SOME_KINDA_SECRET_TECHNIQUE                        = 10921,  -- 'N openin' 'em requires some kinda secret technique. Maybe it'll succeed, maybe tha box'll break. 'Sif I know. But ya can only try 'em once a day.
        OHO_YA_FEELIN_LUCKY_NOUGH_TAH_TAKES_A                                   = 10922,  -- Oho, ya feelin' lucky 'nough tah takes a stab at da myst'ry box?
        WHATCHA_GONNA_DO_TALLY_OPEN_THE_BOX_AND                                 = 10923,  -- Whatcha gonna do? (# tally) Open the box and profit! Listen to the explanation. Inquire about my daily tally. Peek at some possibilities. Nothing right now.
        YA_WANNA_OPEN_DAT_SUCKER_UP_OKAY_BUT                                    = 10924,  -- Ya wanna open dat sucker up? Okay, but which dial ya be wantin'?
        DAT_S_DA_SPIRIT_SO_WHICH_DIAL_YA                                        = 10925,  -- Dat's da spirit! So which dial ya be wantin'?
        SO_WHAT_DIAL_YA_GONNA_PICK_TALLY_I                                      = 10926,  -- So, what dial ya gonna pick? (# tally) I got cold feet, so none. Dial 1 (Materials): # tally. Dial 2 (Food): # tally. Dial 3 (Medicine): # tally. Dial 4 (Sundries 1): # tally. Dial 5 (Sundries 2): # tally. Special dial: # tally [/ (already opened)]. Adoulin dial: # tally[/ (already opened)]. Pictlogica dial: # tally[/ (already opened)]. @ @ @ Wanted dial: # tally[/ (already opened)]. @ @
        YER_GOIN_WIT_DIAL_HUH_WHATCHU_TRYIN_TA                                  = 10927,  -- Yer goin' wit' dial #, huh? Whatchu tryin' ta pull!? Yer daily tally's too low.
        YER_GOIN_WIT_DIAL_HUH_LESSEE_WHAT_MYST                                  = 10928,  -- Yer goin' wit' dial #, huh? Lessee what myst'ries await!
        DIS_BOX_IS_FULL_O_MYST_RIES_T                                           = 10929,  -- Dis box is full o' myst'ries,t Dat span da realm's his'try,t So whatcha gonna get from da chest...o'...uh, fortunery?t
        OOOH_LOOKS_AT_WHAT_POPPED_OUT_I_HOPES                                   = 10930,  -- Oooh, looks at what popped out! I hopes it makes yer adventures dat much more adventumarous!
        YA_S_THOUGHT_I_THREW_YER_PRIZE_AWAY                                     = 10931,  -- Ya's thought I threw yer prize away?! Prepostamarous! I's just tucked it away for safekeepin' is all.
